Since you're new here, there are a few things I need to explain first.
I'll take care of logistics, and everything else out there is in your hands.
This\ is\ the\ Warehouse\.\ You\ can\ store\ your\ items\ here\.
This is the Construction Panel. You can build or dismantle facilities from here.

This is the Bunker Exit. You'll be heading out from here.
We don't have much to our name right now, so bring back as much as you can.
Before heading out, don't forget—I've got some quests for you.
Hunger, in Duckov, is a real threat.
Keep an eye on your Energy and Hydration.
See if you can find something to eat. I'm getting hungry too.
Do you still remember what you look like?
Don't wander off! This dream's full of invisible walls!

Find the right materials, and it'll enhance your abilities.

Enemies ahead! Melee weapons work best on red ducks — even easier if you know how to dodge.
If you want to head back, you can return to the Bunker from here.
And if you're further out, just find some green smoke. That'll bring you back too.
Here, take this wooden stick, for protection. Better than nothing, huh?
I see great potential in you. How about learning Body Training from me?
Body Training makes you stronger and smarter!
Come! Master's got your first challenge ready!

Bring me a pack of smokes! This is your final trial!
Well done. You've passed my trials with flying colors.
I've decided. I'm moving in with you.
Build a gym at your place, and I will move in.
One misstep... a lifetime of regret.

Actually, you can go get them back yourself next time.

Unlock to purchase {ItemDisplayName} from the shop.
Medical supplies are essential in Duckov. I need some small medkits right now. You can either search for them or craft them at the Medic Station.
Your first task is simple: prove you can make it back alive.
Before you arrived, we sent an advance team into Duckov, but we haven't heard from them. Their safe house is located inside a building in the factory area. Can you check it out?
According to the advance team, J-Lab employees used to live in a dormitory building in the woods. Could you check out the situation there?

It seems J-Lab evacuated in a hurry. When we checked the lab earlier, all the data had been destroyed, but they probably didn't have time to deal with the data in the dormitory. Please make another trip and copy all the computer files for me. Don't forget to bring a portable hard drive before you go.

Bleeding is serious. While it won't kill you right away, you'll keep taking damage if not treated quickly. Bandages are the simplest way to control bleeding—try using them. If you can't find any, you can buy some from the vending machine.
I'm hungry, let's get some food.

A crow we've been monitoring, Blackie, met with another mysterious crow at the gas station. We need to know what they discussed. Can you help us retrieve the surveillance footage? Don't forget your portable hard drive!
Check the power facilities in the warehouse.
Check a power facility in the dock warehouse.

The data you brought back seems to be encrypted, and we can't extract the key information. We need some J-Lab floppy disks for decryption. Could you help us find one? They're not too rare and could be found in any location J-Lab personnel have visited.

We've decrypted the gas station data. The person we met seems to be a messenger, here to inform us about the attack on J-Lab. It looks like the incident at J-Lab is indeed tied to these crows. We need to find more information on this messenger. He's said to have visited a customs office. Could you check it out? Maybe this place is more than just a food factory?

This place is so dull. It would be a whole lot more fun if there was a gaming console. Could you get me an FC (Future Computer) console? I've got an FC cartridge with me. Oh, and don't forget to bring back a controller.
The gaming console you brought me is broken, but no worries! Help me find some parts, and I'll be able to fix it.
Break Tom's high score in Breakout.
There was this insanely popular game called Block Dragon back then. I could never reach 1,000 points, and it became my obsession. Could you help me find a copy of Block Dragon?
Wow, this old monochrome TV is completely useless for playing Block Dragon! Could you help me find some parts?

I finally hit 1,000 points! But I'm tired of this game now. Feel free to give it a try and see if you can beat my record! By the way, when I was younger, I always wanted to play a game called Duck Land. I saw adults having so much fun with it. Could you help me find one?
Duck World needs a memory card? Otherwise, I'll have to start all over every time I power off. That's going to be so frustrating! Please help me find a memory card!
Assembling the game console is fun too! This time, I'll let you have the fun! And you can try the game as well!

Collect two pieces of wood to build a Workbench. There are enemies around, so don't wander too far. Once you have the materials, check the construction panel next to the vending machine. I'll leave your rewards in the delivery locker.
Based on available information, we've located some J-Lab supplies inside the factory area. Entry requires a keycard, which may be found on the elite crows.
Thanks to you fixing the signal tower, I've made contact with an old friend. He's a weapon merchant who offered to come if we set up a weapon shop here.
I've contacted my old friend. He's an equipment merchant with many connections. Once you set up the shop, he'll come.
A blade under the bed can help you sleep with peace of mind.
You've gathered quite a few items, and space is running low. Time to expand the warehouse.
Producing our own medical supplies would make things much easier.
Let's see how well the new medic station works.
With a teleporter, we won't have to start from the Bunker every time. We need to find the blueprint and build one. Last I heard, it's in the cave. Don't forget a Shovel!
Bring me a few Pistols to study. If all goes well, you'll be able to buy them from the Vending Machine later.
Make\ sure\ the\ muscular\ duck\ gets\ enough\ protein\.
Make\ sure\ the\ muscular\ duck\ gets\ enough\ carbs\.
Take\ care\ of\ the\ muscular\ duck's\ mental\ wellbeing\.
Build a proper gym for Mud at the Base.
My supplier's been short on raw materials lately. We could turn this into a profit. Get it done, and I'll sell you an AK-74U at a better price.
Figure out how to get the beacon key to Farm Town. If I'm right, it's stored on a computer at the road camp. Bring a Portable Hard Drive and copy the data.
I need a Pocket Watch right now—don't ask why. It's in a tank truck at the far east end of Ground Zero. I lost the key, so you'll have to find it and bring back the watch.
Scavengers hijacked some valuable cargo near the northwest edge of Ground Zero. I want to know what's inside. See if you can find the cargo list—it's probably in one of the containers.
I'm new around here and still finding my way. Can you help me locate two fishing docks in Ground Zero?

If\ you\ have\ the\ right\ gear,\ you\ can\ take\ on\ those\ rampaging\ scavengers—the\ red\ ones\ with\ butcher\ knives\.\ Once\ you're\ done,\ I'll\ leave\ some\ bolts\ and\ nuts\ in\ the\ delivery\ locker\.\ You\ can\ use\ them\ to\ upgrade\ the\ workbench\.
Help me run a field test on the AK-74U's performance.
Those black ducks have wrecked too much of our infrastructure. It's time they learned a lesson.
To expand our range of activities, we need to build a teleporter. After years of research, I know how to make one. The only problem is, I don't have the materials.
Have you seen those glowing feathers on the creatures out there? They seem useful. Help me gather some for research.

I arranged for merchants to deliver supplies, but the signal tower northeast of our hideout seems broken, and I can't contact them. Could you fix it? Bring a flathead screwdriver – you can get one at the nearby vending machine.
I\ received\ a\ letter\ from\ a\ friend,\ which\ I\ left\ in\ the\ red\ tent\ on\ Small\ Hill\.\ It\ contains\ his\ contact\ information\.\ I\ need\ to\ find\ him\ urgently\.

We're\ planning\ a\ new\ business\ in\ the\ Warehouse\ Area,\ so\ we\ need\ you\ to\ scout\ it\ first\.\ The\ zipline\ at\ the\ top\ of\ North\ Mountain\ in\ Ground\ Zero\ should\ lead\ there\.\ Gear\ up\ and\ scout\ the\ path\.\ You\ can\ blast\ through\ the\ walls\ with\ grenades\ or\ explosives\.\ Don't\ push\ too\ hard\.\ Just\ come\ back\ safe\.
Black ducks are crawling all over the Warehouse Area—dangerous types. Can you take out a few using the weapon I provide?
Someone said bows are worthless. As a bow lover, I can't let that slide. Prove them wrong, and I'll reward you with a sniper rifle.

There's\ something\ shady\ going\ on\ at\ a\ certain\ beverage\ factory\.\ Near\ the\ Lumber\ Mill\ in\ the\ Warehouse\ Area,\ there's\ a\ water\ tower\ hiding\ their\ secret\ ingredients\.\ Something\ leaked\ recently—grab\ a\ few\ samples\.
Heard you've been to the warehouse area. A friend told me there's a great fishing spot there. Think you can find it for me?

I\ have\ an\ informant,\ a\ demolitions\ expert,\ who\ knows\ the\ Warehouse\ Area\ well\.\ I've\ lost\ contact\ with\ him\.\ Check\ his\ old\ place—a\ green\ house\ in\ the\ corner\ south\ of\ the\ Ravine,\ See\ if\ he's\ still\ around\.
Looks\ like\ you're\ settling\ in\ well\.\ Time\ to\ test\ your\ skills—take\ down\ Pato\ Chapo\ at\ the\ Road\ Camp\.

The\ safehouse\ in\ the\ Warehouse\ Area\ is\ having\ power\ issues\.\ It's\ near\ a\ house\ by\ a\ small\ hill,\ just\ north\ of\ the\ broken\ bridge\.\ Or\ you\ could\ say\ it's\ northeast\ of\ the\ Farmhouse\.\ Bring\ a\ Wrench\ before\ you\ go\.
Fix\ the\ safehouse\ power\ supply\ in\ the\ Warehouse\ Area\.
There's\ a\ freak\ in\ the\ Warehouse\ Area—comes\ and\ goes\ like\ a\ ghost,\ always\ with\ a\ dog\ by\ his\ side\.\ And\ he\ usually\ snipes\ from\ miles\ away\.\ Teach\ him\ a\ lesson\.

Archery\ didn't\ even\ slow\ you\ down\.\ Now,\ my\ friend\ says\ there's\ no\ way\ you\ can\ take\ down\ those\ mercs\ with\ a\ butcher\ knife\.\ I'm\ betting\ ten\ grand\ you'll\ prove\ them\ wrong\.
One\ of\ my\ clients\ is\ lying\ low\ at\ the\ Farmhouse\ in\ the\ Warehouse\ Area,\ but\ they're\ running\ out\ of\ water\.\ Could\ you\ bring\ them\ some\?\ Leave\ three\ bottles\ in\ the\ shed\.
Stash the bottled water at the marked spot.
Congratulations,\ you've\ unlocked\ all\ talents!\ Let's\ build\ a\ Commemorative\ Trophy!
Collect\ samples\ from\ the\ water\ tower\ in\ the\ Lumber\ Mill\.
I know a dev (not me, I swear) who's been acting weird lately—keeps muttering “Please add to your Wishlist, please!” over and over. He's a nice guy... not sure what happened. Mind helping them out?
The Western Factory is the heart of the Warehouse Area. It's full of valuable stuff—and danger. There are three entrances to the area. I need you to scout them all.
Happy New Year! Let's put up some festive decorations!
This item will be lost when you return to the Bunker.
Used at the Advanced Workbench to craft items.

A civilian variant of a service rifle. While less powerful, it offers superior stability and broader attachment compatibility.

A service SMG with high accuracy and low recoil, making it ideal for hip fire.
A simply built service rifle with decent accuracy. In Duckov, high-powered rifles are classified as battle rifles and require different ammo—despite using the same caliber. No one knows why.
A manually loaded double-barrel shotgun, commonly used for self-defense.
A single-barrel shotgun fed by a detachable magazine.

Equipped with a built-in suppressor and optical sight. Ideal for ambushes, but limited in effective range.

A modular service battle rifle still under testing. For unknown reasons, its removable barrel is permanently fixed with a black casing.
An MP7 with a battery—fires electric bullets. Duckstar Tech at its most electrifying.

About\ the\ spacecraft's\ life\ support\ system,\ I've\ got\ an\ informant\ with\ some\ intel\.\ But\ he\ has\ a\ condition:\ He\ wants\ an\ Electrified\ MP7\.\ I\ remember\ the\ Speedy\ Group\ Commander\ in\ the\ Warehouse\ Area\ has\ one\.

About\ the\ life\ support\ system\ I\ mentioned,\ my\ informant\ can't\ show\ up\ in\ person,\ so\ he\ left\ the\ intel\ in\ the\ Warehouse\ Area\.\ When\ you\ head\ there,\ bring\ it\ back\ for\ me\.\ It's\ stashed\ in\ a\ blue\ safehouse\ near\ the\ broken\ bridge\.

We've\ pinpointed\ the\ locations\ of\ the\ life\ support\ pods\.\ Take\ the\ Marker\ to\ the\ Warehouse\ Area\ and\ mark\ them\.\ I'll\ have\ someone\ remove\ the\ life\ support\ device\ inside\.\ The\ first\ pod\ is\ in\ a\ house\ on\ the\ northern\ side\ of\ the\ East\ Road\ Camp\.\ The\ second\ is\ inside\ a\ yellow\ container\ at\ the\ Lumber\ Mill\.\ The\ third\ is\ in\ another\ yellow\ container\ near\ a\ house\ south\ of\ the\ Ravine\.\ The\ fourth\ is\ located\ in\ the\ Western\ Factory\ office\.
The\ life\ support\ pods\ are\ back,\ but\ some\ are\ a\ little\ banged\ up\.\ Help\ me\ gather\ some\ materials\ to\ patch\ it\ up\.
Besides the pods, the life support system also needs a circulation unit. According to the intel, it's in a factory on the southeastern edge of Farm Town. Go check it out and bring it back.
I'm trying to build a machine to serve as the spacecraft's computing hub. Still need some basic parts—see if you've got any spares.

Turns\ out\ the\ DIY\ machine's\ pretty\ weak\ in\ the\ computing\ department\.\ I'll\ keep\ it\.\.\.\ for\ research\.\ Head\ to\ the\ Mine\ in\ Farm\ Town—it's\ east\ of\ the\ Sanatorium\.\ See\ if\ there's\ anything\ more\ powerful\ we\ can\ use\.\ If\ you\ can't\ get\ in,\ try\ the\ nearby\ gas\ station\.\ Oh,\ and\ don't\ forget\ to\ bring\ the\ Marker\.
That\ supercomputer\ draws\ a\ ton\ of\ power,\ and\ it\ needs\ serious\ cooling\ to\ keep\ up\.\ I\ remember\ seeing\ a\ cooling\ unit\ in\ a\ house\ not\ far\ from\ the\ Hidden\ Mine\.
I've finished analyzing the supercomputer. Most of its parts are toast—we'll need replacements. First, let's find a motherboard that can fit all these parts. There should be one in that Mine.

Got\ an\ anonymous\ letter\ last\ night\.\ Check\ this\ out:\ "I've\ got\ info\ about\ the\ vector\ thruster\ you're\ after\.\ Help\ me\ find\ and\ mark\ my\ stolen\ car,\ and\ I'll\ share\ it\."\ I\ checked—his\ car\ should\ be\ to\ the\ east\ of\ Farm\ Town\ City\ Hall's\ plaza\.\ It's\ a\ black\ SUV\.
Got a reply—check this out: "Thanks. The info you want is on a computer on the second floor of the Office Building. It's right in the center of Farm Town. Don't forget a Portable Hard Drive."

I\ decrypted\ the\ hard\ drive\ data,\ which\ contains\ leads\ on\ the\ thruster\ research\.\ The\ researcher\ lives\ in\ a\ two-story\ cabin\ east\ of\ the\ Abandoned\ Construction\ Site\ in\ Farm\ Town\.\ He's\ got\ a\ habit\ of\ hiding\ keys\ nearby\.\ Let's\ search\ the\ place\.\ We\ might\ find\ what\ we're\ after\.
We\ managed\ to\ secure\ the\ thruster\ design\ data,\ but\ we're\ still\ short\ of\ some\ materials\.\ Could\ you\ help\ gather\ them\?

For\ interstellar\ travel,\ the\ navigation\ system\ is\ absolutely\ essential\.\ We\ need\ the\ ship's\ design\ schematics\.\ Based\ on\ solid\ intel,\ they're\ locked\ in\ a\ safe\ at\ the\ Ground\ Zero\ Road\ Camp\.\ The\ key\ should\ be\ hidden\ somewhere\ inside\ a\ building\ in\ the\ Warehouse\ Area\.\ Find\ a\ way\ to\ get\ those\ schematics\.
Now that we've got the schematics, we'll need some key materials to finish the job. I'm missing a few—see what you can dig up.

I learned that a rogue scientist developed a low-cost way to generate defense fields. The blueprint is in his room—Dorm 101, Construction Site, Farm Town. With that, we won't have to worry about getting pelted by those small stones on the way.
The\ Blueprint\ of\ Defense\ Field\ is\ decrypted,\ and\ the\ materials\ are\ nothing\ fancy\.\ Go\ find\ what\ we\ need\.

The\ defense\ field\ set\ up\ earlier\ got\ wrecked\ after\ just\ a\ couple\ of\ stray\ shots\.\ Cost\ me\ a\ pretty\ penny\.\ However,\ I\ heard\ there's\ a\ legit\ one\ in\ J-Lab's\ B2\.\ Why\ don't\ you\ go\ get\ it\?\ Make\ sure\ you're\ well-prepared\ though\.\ That\ place\ isn't\ safe\.
Interstellar\ travel\ requires\ plenty\ of\ energy\.\ Storm\ Creature\ crystals\ are\ perfect\ for\ this!\ Gather\ some\ for\ me\.
The clue our informant left is barely readable. Honestly, feels like only Jeff can make sense of it.
Use the Marker to tag Life Support Pod 1.
A coordinate-emitting device powered by solar energy and... egg whites? Rumor has it this thing can last up to 10,000 years.
Use the Marker to tag Life Support Pod 2.
Use the Marker to tag Life Support Pod 3.
A vital part of the spacecraft's life support system.
Delivers up to 1 EFLOPS of computing power.

Maximizes the performance of the High-Performance Computing Unit.
Still has traces of blood on it.
Highly encrypted, completely unreadable to non-experts.

One-time pass. Grants access to the lab's core area.
One-time pass with the highest authority. Grants access to classified zones.
Details the vector thruster test process. No results or blueprints included. The rest is strangely meticulous, as if the writer had a terrible memory.
Intact—because the head wasn't blown off.

A durable plastic sheet that's difficult to decompose.
Encrypted blueprint for a top-tier cosmic defense field, essential for space travel.
Got a tip on how to weaken the defense field: set up four high-energy 5G antennas around it, then find a way to temporarily resist space storms. That should get you in.
Matter leaking from the rift holds massive energy, but it's tough to harness directly.
A special device that reconstructs egg-white-based energy. Its mechanism and origin remain unknown.
Reconstructed egg-white energy. More stable, easier to harness, and immensely powerful.
A blueprint for developing High-Performance Computing Units, encrypted with complex algorithms and nearly indecipherable.
A high-output power supply with a large red star stamped on the side.
Features massive cooling fins and fans, but oddly, only two heat pipes.

Also,\ find\ a\ high-capacity\ power\ supply—it's\ a\ real\ power\ hog\.\ A\ buddy\ of\ mine\ wanted\ to\ build\ a\ super\ PC\ but\ couldn't\ afford\ it,\ so\ he\ just\ bought\ the\ power\ supply\ first\.\ He\ hid\ it\ in\ that\ town\ northeast\ of\ Farm\ Town,\ by\ the\ cave\ that\ connects\ to\ the\ Warehouse\ Area\.\ Bring\ a\ Shovel\ and\ dig\ it\ up\.\ He\ won't\ mind\.
A supercomputer can't function without its core—but gathering the materials won't be easy. This one's going to be tough.
No clue who this key belongs to.
Many secrets lie hidden beneath its surface.
There's\ a\ mysterious\ door\ in\ the\ basement\ of\ the\ Farm\ Town\ Office\ Building\.\ Go\ check\ it\ out\.\ It\ might\ be\ hiding\ something\ valuable\.

Our\ hideout\ is\ taking\ shape\.\ Time\ to\ venture\ into\ the\ stars\ and\ seas!\ Building\ our\ Teleporter\ is\ step\ one\.\ With\ it,\ we\ can\ instantly\ jump\ to\ other\ regions—provided\ you've\ activated\ their\ beacons\ first\.

Now that we've built our own teleporter, let's unlock the Ground Zero beacon. These beacons allow free teleportation—though the coordinates are... less than stable. Intel says the beacon's at the road camp. It's risky, so stay sharp.
We're\ finally\ heading\ farther\ out\.\ To\ make\ trips\ to\ the\ Warehouse\ Area\ faster,\ you\ need\ to\ activate\ the\ teleport\ beacon\ beside\ the\ Gas\ Station\ in\ the\ Warehouse\ Area\.

There\ are\ two\ beacons\ in\ Farm\ Town\.\ I\ need\ you\ to\ unlock\ the\ northern\ one—it's\ just\ north\ of\ the\ Hillside\ Farmhouse\.\ Take\ the\ northern\ passage\ from\ the\ Warehouse\ Area\ to\ get\ there\.\ You'll\ need\ 2\ Dynamites\ to\ get\ through\.
Nice spot you found! My rod broke a few days ago—think you could help me fix it up and maybe upgrade it too?
Heard night fishing (22:00–05:00) brings better luck, but it's risky after dark. Could you check out the fish population at the Farm Town dock? And most importantly, bring a flashlight!
Ever since I got my new rod, I haven't missed a single catch! Don't believe me? Hand me a bucket—I'll bring it back full.
Armored suit with boosted fire resistance. Doesn't offer much protection against bullets, but greatly reduces fire DMG.
Civilian-grade jacket made of tough leather. Offers decent protection against shoddy bullets.

I\ ordered\ some\ new\ goods,\ but\ the\ supplier\ just\ told\ me\ they\ were\ robbed\ halfway\.\ The\ goods\ were\ lost\ near\ the\ Forest\ Path\ in\ Ground\ Zero,\ by\ a\ campfire\ tent\.\ Head\ over\ there\ and\ mark\ the\ spot—don't\ forget\ to\ bring\ a\ Marker\.\ I'll\ make\ it\ worth\ your\ while\.\ If\ you\ don't\ have\ one,\ try\ the\ vending\ machine\ or\ ask\ Xiaoming\.

If you want to survive out here, you need to shoot straight. Land 5 headshots—any enemy will do. How? Just aim for the head. You can practice at the shooting range nearby. Don't worry, ammo isn't consumed in the hideout.
Check the fishing spot with a flashlight.

Training\ could\ really\ use\ a\ boost,\ but\ I'm\ short\ on\ materials\.\ Bring\ me\ what\ I\ need,\ and\ I'll\ whip\ up\ two\ doses\ for\ you\ too\.

Been needing a lot of raw materials lately. Buying all the time won't cut it. Get me some UV lights—I'll start growing my own.

I've\ been\ working\ on\ something\ new\ and\ need\ field\ data\.\ Use\ a\ Melee\ Injector\ to\ take\ down\ 5\ green\ ducks\.\ That\ will\ help\ with\ my\ research\.
Not bad—you've reached 10% of my physical prowess. Keep it up, and you might just survive what's coming next.
Time\ to\ put\ that\ strength\ to\ the\ test\.\ Go\ beat\ up\ that\ yellow\ duck!
Thanks to you dealing with those mercs, my supply routes are running much smoother. But now we're short on logistics crates. Can you help me with that?
Plant the dynamite at the rock pile.

A client wants to blow open the western wall of the Warehouse Area. Apparently, there's a hidden passage leading to town. They've asked us to provide the explosives. Just take the dynamite and plant it at the rock pile along the western wall. You'll know it when you see it.

We're\ running\ dangerously\ low\ on\ fuel\.\ Head\ to\ the\ Warehouse\ Area\ and\ extract\ fuel\ from\ the\ tank\ trucks\.\ There's\ one\ each\ in\ the\ northeast\ and\ southwest\ of\ the\ Western\ Factory,\ one\ near\ the\ Lumber\ Mill,\ and\ one\ more\ in\ East\ Road\ Camp\.

Farm\ Town's\ a\ good\ source\ for\ loot—malls,\ restaurants,\ and\ schools\ hide\ plenty\ of\ goodies\.\ I\ recommend\ taking\ the\ breach\ in\ the\ Western\ Factory\ wall\.\ Some\ oddball\ collapsed\ the\ path\ with\ rubble\.\ 2\ Dynamites\ will\ clear\ it,\ and\ you\ can\ reach\ Farm\ Town\.

Did\ you\ hear\?\ The\ latest\ bodybuilding\ competition\ added\ a\ "Storm\ Endurance"\ program\.\ I\ gave\ it\ a\ try—it's\ brutal\.\ I\ need\ some\ research\ materials\.\ Take\ down\ a\ Spider-Bot\ at\ night,\ bring\ back\ its\ Computing\ Core,\ and\ grab\ some\ Cold\ Core\ Fragments\.\ Don't\ worry,\ I'll\ share\ the\ results\ with\ you\.

The samples you collected have greatly helped my research, but further experiments require higher concentrations of storm energy. Within the storm dwell unique creatures that drop Space Crystals, ideal for my work. Regular bullets are largely ineffective against them. Use elemental weapons whenever you can.
A recipe used to craft Contaminated Weapon Parts at the Workbench.
Aim for the head! It's their weak spot.
A\ recipe\ for\ crafting\ the\ Expansion\ Crate\ \(L\)\ at\ the\ Workbench\.
You've proven yourself. I've asked Xavier to bring in some M700s for you. Now begins the premium sniper trial. Go, and bring back some good news.
You\ didn't\ let\ me\ down\.\ Now\ for\ the\ final\ test:\ score\ two\ headshots\ each\ on\ Mad\ Bomber,\ Triple-Shot\ Man,\ and\ Security\ Captain\.\ Prove\ yourself,\ and\ the\ weapon\ is\ yours\.
I haven't slept a wink thanks to those damn mosquitoes. The cannon's ready—just need some gunpowder. Dismantle some standard ammo at the Workbench and let's end this buzzing nightmare.
Last session's save was corrupted. Restored to the latest available version. Some progress may be lost.

New\ anonymous\ message:\ "Thanks\ for\ recovering\ my\ car\.\ Those\ damn\ black\ ducks\ stole\ it\.\ Since\ you've\ come\ this\ far,\ why\ not\ help\ me\ get\ revenge\?\ Don't\ worry\ about\ retaliation—use\ the\ Electrified\ MP7\ and\ pin\ it\ on\ that\ yellow\ duck\ in\ the\ Warehouse\ Area\."\ Help\ them\ out\.\ Completing\ this\ mission\ should\ get\ us\ intel\ on\ the\ thruster\.
Generates a high-energy defensive field to counter space debris during interstellar travel.

I\ do\ part-time\ courier\ runs—it's\ not\ just\ cool,\ it\ pays\ well\ too\.\ Bet\ you'd\ be\ interested\.\ Getting\ started\ is\ easy\.\ Grab\ the\ package\ from\ the\ red\ truck\ by\ the\ Lumber\ Mill\ in\ the\ Warehouse\ Area,\ then\ drop\ it\ off\ at\ the\ red\ truck\ near\ the\ Gas\ Station\.
Secure the package and complete the delivery.
Secure the package and complete the delivery.

New assignment! Head to the chimney in the Western Factory in Warehouse Area, pick up the package, and deliver it to the green house near the East Road Camp. Complete this one and you'll be promoted to Senior Courier!

You've\ done\ an\ excellent\ job\ so\ far,\ but\ to\ truly\ become\ an\ Expert\ Courier\ and\ start\ earning\ serious\ money,\ you'll\ need\ to\ boost\ your\ efficiency\.\ Try\ handling\ two\ deliveries\ in\ one\ run:\ the\ first\ package\ goes\ from\ the\ cabin\ near\ the\ Farm\ Town\ Sawmill\ to\ the\ dried-up\ well\ beside\ the\ Farmhouse\.\ And\ the\ second\ from\ the\ guard\ room\ by\ the\ east\ gate\ of\ the\ Northern\ Factory\ to\ the\ room\ on\ the\ east\ side\ of\ the\ Sanatorium\.\ Plan\ your\ route\ wisely\ to\ make\ the\ most\ of\ your\ time\.
Secure the first package and complete the delivery.
Secure the second package and complete the delivery.

As\ an\ Expert\ Courier,\ you're\ now\ trusted\ with\ cross-regional\ deliveries\.\ This\ one\ starts\ from\ the\ deep\ Cellar\ in\ the\ Warehouse\ Area\ and\ ends\ at\ the\ office\ inside\ the\ southeastern\ Chemical\ Plant\ in\ Farm\ Town\.\ Both\ locations\ are\ affected\ by\ gas\ leaks,\ so\ don't\ forget\ to\ wear\ your\ Gas\ Mask!
Custom AK-47. Cannot be brought back to Base.

This job is notoriously difficult. Many expert couriers have failed. Pick up the custom AK-47 from the blue truck north of the Ground Zero road camp, use it to eliminate the Speedy Group Commander in the Warehouse Area, and then deliver the weapon to the arcade entrance in Farm Town's commercial district. Don't forget to bring extra AR ammo. Good luck, I'm counting on you.
You've become the benchmark for all couriers. It's time to entrust you with the ultimate delivery mission.
Custom StG 77A3. Cannot be brought back to Base.
Custom M14. Cannot be brought back to Base.
Custom Glick. Cannot be brought back to Base.
Custom MP-155. Cannot be brought back to Base.
Custom SR-3M. Cannot be brought back to Base.
Custom Mosin-Nagant. Cannot be brought back to Base.

Rumor\ has\ it\ that\ many\ J-Lab\ researchers\ graduated\ from\ the\ School\ in\ Farm\ Town\.\ Find\ the\ headmaster's\ office\ and\ retrieve\ the\ graduate\ list\.\ It\ might\ prove\ useful\ someday\.
A list of graduates from the Farm Town school.
A key to the headmaster's office at the Farm Town school.
Formulated with a special recipe, remarkably effective at scrubbing toilets clean.
There's\ a\ special\ kind\ of\ toilet\ cleaner\ at\ the\ Supermarket\ in\ Farm\ Town\.\ I\ really\ need\ it\.\ Bring\ me\ three\ bottles,\ please\.
My\ legs\ are\ killing\ me\.\ Maybe\ I've\ been\ overmedicating\.\ There's\ some\ leg\ pain\ medicine\ at\ the\ Red\ Duck\ Camp\ in\ Ground\ Zero\.\ Could\ you\ bring\ it\ back\ for\ me\?
Now,\ my\ hands\ hurt\.\ Pain\ medicine\ for\ hands\ is\ hidden\ in\ the\ green\ house\ south\ of\ the\ Ravine\ in\ the\ Warehouse\ Area\.\ Bring\ it\ quickly\.

That\ last\ headache\ pill\ didn't\ do\ much\.\ Try\ grabbing\ some\ stronger\ painkillers\ from\ the\ Sanatorium\ in\ Farm\ Town\.\ Maybe\ we\ just\ didn't\ take\ out\ enough\ black\ ducks\ —\ handle\ a\ few\ more\ while\ you're\ at\ it\.
A specific painkiller. Doesn't just kill the pain, it kills all sensation.
Supposedly great for headaches, or so the label claims.
Targeted relief for fingertip pain, according to the label.
Supposedly for leg pain, but judging by the ingredients, it's basically just calcium tablets.
Double\ strength\ protein\ powder,\ that's\ what\ it\ says\ on\ the\ label\.
I think I've figured out how to duplicate the J-Lab Level 1 pass, but I'll need some originals to analyze. Bring me a few and I should be able to make it work.

Please\ note\ that\ this\ difficulty\ cannot\ be\ changed\ once\ selected\.
Enemies\ deal\ 175%\ DMG\.
Enemies\ have\ 40%\ HP\.
Enemies\ reaction\ speed\ is\ largely\ increased\.
Lost\ gear\ will\ be\ gone\ for\ good\.
Bleed\ status\ will\ not\ be\ removed\ automatically\.
Fracture\ and\ Wound\ effects\ are\ added\.

Suitable\ for\ players\ familiar\ with\ this\ game\.
Enemies\ deal\ 100%\ DMG\.
Enemies\ have\ 100%\ HP\.
Enemy\ reaction\ speed\ is\ slightly\ increased\.
Timber\ prices\ are\ soaring\.\ The\ lumber\ mills\ could\ be\ lucrative\.\ They're\ in\ both\ the\ Warehouse\ Area\ and\ Farm\ Town\.\ I\ need\ you\ to\ do\ a\ field\ survey\.
Reduces Fire DMG taken for a period of time.
Reduces Poison DMG taken for a period of time.
Reduces Space DMG taken for a period of time, but doesn't shield you from Space Storm.
You did well last time, but I'm still not satisfied. Take my weapon—go teach them another lesson.
I'm fed up with those red ducks—and I bet you are too. Eye for an eye. Do to them exactly what they did to us.
Good, you passed my test. Now for your sniper certification. A real sniper must first master the pistol—and yes, headshots are a must.
This is a real test, so we need real targets. Get two headshot kills on Pato Chapo using the SKS.

Not bad—I'll admit it, you're a sniper now. But a sniper needs the right weapon. There's a guy named Lordon in the Warehouse Area. His rifle's solid. Bring it to me and I'll tune it up. Just remember: a true sniper always goes for the head. I suggest the StG-77.
You've got yourself a proper sniper rifle. Time to prove you deserve it. And don't lose it, unless you want to go begging Lorden for another one.
Craft an MF and put its power to the test.
You've proven yourself. I've asked Xavier to bring in some M700s for you. Now begins the premium sniper trial. Go, and bring back some good news.
Even\ a\ top-tier\ sniper\ can't\ neglect\ the\ pistol\.\ Use\ the\ Glick\ to\ take\ out\ some\ black\ ducks\ in\ Farm\ Town\.
Too heavy to be taken back to Base.
Congrats\ on\ passing\ the\ premium\ sniper\ test\.\ Your\ first\ task:\ eliminate\ a\ tough\ target\ near\ the\ Supermarket\ in\ Farm\ Town\.\ Show\ us\ what\ you're\ made\ of\.
AK-47 and MF are both common here. Let's compare how they perform—use the black ducks in Farm Town as your test subjects.

They\ say\ that\ there's\ an\ insanely\ fast\ yellow\ duck\ in\ the\ Warehouse\ Area\.\ I'm\ not\ convinced—hit\ yourself\ with\ a\ Yellow\ Injector\ and\ race\ him\.\ Just\ be\ sure\ to\ finish\ him\ off\ while\ the\ effect\ is\ active,\ or\ we\ won't\ be\ able\ to\ prove\ my\ potion\ works\.
A supplier recommended the StG-77 to me, but I'm not sold yet. If you've got one, try it out in Farm Town. If it performs well, I'll place an order.
The workbench has plenty of uses. Why not upgrade it and see what it can do?
I've\ hired\ the\ cook,\ but\ you\ can't\ make\ a\ feast\ without\ a\ kitchen\.\ Get\ him\ a\ place\ to\ cook\.
A tech-savvy friend reached out—he wants in on our team. He stashed his gear in a yellow bus on the Ground Zero highway. Go grab the stuff and use it to set up a Tech Center.

I've\ got\ a\ gym\ buddy\ living\ in\ the\ Office\ Building\ Apartment\ in\ Farm\ Town\.\ Haven't\ heard\ from\ him\ in\ a\ while—can\ you\ check\ on\ him\?\ Oh,\ and\ I'm\ running\ low\ on\ protein\ powder\.\ He\ should\ have\ some\ at\ his\ place,\ so\ grab\ me\ a\ tub\ while\ you're\ there\.
Game cartridge: Carbonated Danger Duck. The title was inspired by test subjects in J-Lab.
Releases a toxic cloud that poisons enemies, inflicting continuous DMG.
If\ no\ DMG\ is\ taken\ for\ 10\ seconds,\ it\ slowly\ restores\ a\ large\ amount\ of\ HP,\ but\ increases\ Hydration\ and\ Energy\ Cost\ Rate\.
Immune to Shatter effect caused by space bullets, but cannot resist space storms. And Max HP is reduced.
Immune to Shatter effect caused by space bullets, but cannot resist space storms.

The\ navigation\ system\ is\ ready,\ but\ hardware\ alone\ isn't\ enough\ for\ interstellar\ travel\.\ We\ need\ a\ Star\ Map\ to\ chart\ the\ course\.\ They\ must\ have\ left\ the\ data\ behind\ before\ they\ evacuated\.\ Take\ the\ Portable\ Hard\ Drive\ to\ the\ office\ in\ Zone\ 9\ of\ the\ J-Lab\ and\ download\ the\ Star\ Map\ data\.

Nailed it last time! The boss was impressed and now there's a new job and better pay. The package is at the green house south of the Ravine. Deliver it to the office inside the red warehouse in the Western Factory. Right beside the two red fuel drums.

Congrats, Senior Courier! We've expanded to Farm Town. Please pick up the package by the tank truck at the Mercenary Camp entrance and deliver it to the red car by the Radar Station. Heads up, this one's heavy and there may be fires nearby. Better put on a fireproof suit and bring a bigger bag!

Cross-regional\ deliveries\ pay\ handsomely\.\ This\ one\ takes\ you\ from\ the\ camp\ by\ the\ Forest\ Path\ in\ Ground\ Zero\ to\ the\ restroom\ door\ on\ the\ first\ floor\ of\ Farm\ Town's\ central\ Office\ Building\.
And now I've got a headache. Head over to the Pharmacy in Farm Town and take out three black ducks. That'll cheer me up.

Thanks\ to\ the\ meds\ you\ fetched,\ I'm\ feeling\ much\ better\ and\ ready\ to\ train\ at\ full\ strength\ again\.\ Before\ he\ went\ missing,\ a\ friend\ mentioned\ a\ powerful\ protein\ powder\.\ I\ want\ to\ try\ it\.\ See\ if\ you\ can\ find\ one\ on\ the\ first\ floor\ of\ the\ Farm\ Town\ Office\ Building\.
That unusual door in J-Lab won't open without a special pass. A lot of researchers used to work at the Mine in Farm Town—you might find something useful there. If you do, bring it back to me.
Two radars in Farm Town are down. Those're our main line of communication. Head over and fix them ASAP, and don't forget to bring two Circuit Boards.

You've\ cleared\ out\ plenty\ of\ black\ ducks\ already,\ but\ they're\ like\ weeds\.\ They\ keep\ coming\ back,\ and\ they're\ back\ to\ disrupting\ my\ supply\ lines\.\ Go\ clear\ out\ some\ more,\ and\ let\ me\ see\ what\ the\ Bizon-2\ can\ do\.\ If\ you\ don't\ have\ one,\ craft\ it\ at\ the\ Workbench—the\ blueprint\ should\ be\ stashed\ somewhere\ in\ the\ Warehouse\ Area\.

An\ excellent\ sniper\ also\ needs\ exceptional\ stamina\ and\ stealth\.\ There's\ a\ heavy\ tire\ by\ the\ dump\ truck\ near\ the\ Hillside\ Farmhouse\ in\ Farm\ Town\.\ Take\ it\ to\ the\ red\ container\ to\ the\ west\ of\ the\ Makeshift\ Construction\ Site,\ and\ you'll\ have\ proven\ yourself\.
You've done outstandingly—every sniper should learn from you! Many of our comrades failed their missions at J-Lab. That's why we need someone like you to lead by example.
Did\ you\ know\ there's\ a\ Mine\ east\ of\ Farm\ Town\?\ It\ uses\ advanced\ iris\ locks—you'll\ need\ the\ Mine\ Manager's\ iris\ data\ to\ get\ in\.\ Key\ tip:\ don't\ hit\ him\ in\ the\ face\.
You may not have permission to modify this item.
A modified baseball bat that looks painfully brutal.
Broken down into small chunks—just the right size to stuff into a gun.
It stinks... but something out there seems to like it.
Immune to Ignite and slightly reduces Fire DMG taken.
Reduces firearm recoil and bullet spread.
Dramatically increases firearm headshot DMG, but increases bullet spread.
Dramatically increases firearm DMG, but reduces range.
Largely increases firearm range and visual range, but slightly reduces movement speed.
Dramatically increases Max HP, but slightly reduces movement speed.
A blueprint used to craft Poop Bullets.
Fireproof work suit made of asbestos. Wearing the full set grants immunity to ground fire damage.
Electric-proof work suit made of rubber. Wearing it grants immunity to ground electrical damage.
Fireproof helmet made of asbestos. Wearing the full set grants immunity to ground fire damage.
A large broken eggshell with traces of egg white inside. Big enough to wear as a helmet.
A\ staff\ apartment\ key\ for\ Room\ 102\.
A\ staff\ apartment\ key\ for\ Room\ 105\.
A\ staff\ apartment\ key\ for\ Room\ 101\.

I\ found\ a\ mysterious\ passage\ in\ a\ house\ south\ of\ the\ Ravine\.\ The\ heavy\ gas\ leak\ makes\ it\ impossible\ to\ check\ properly\.\ If\ you've\ got\ a\ gas\ mask,\ could\ you\ head\ in\ and\ see\ where\ it\ leads\?
A controller for the Future Console. Plug it in to start playing.
A TOZ-66 loaded with Dragon's Breath rounds, firing burning bullets.
There's\ an\ arrogant\ bully\ at\ the\ Farm\ Town\ School\ who\ picks\ on\ the\ weak\.\ Go\ teach\ him\ a\ lesson\ he\ won't\ forget\.

I\ heard\ there's\ a\ hot-blooded\ guy\ at\ school\.\ Go\ challenge\ him!\ A\ real\ tough\ duck\ should\ settle\ it\ with\ a\ real\ fight\.\ But\ to\ keep\ it\ fair,\ you'll\ need\ to\ get\ your\ hands\ on\ that\ special\ bat\ he\ carries\.\ Looks\ like\ he\ customized\ it\ himself,\ and\ it\ packs\ a\ punch\.
Combines 3 Graphics Cards using an advanced method. Although losing some overall performance, they can fit into a single mining machine slot.
A blueprint for unlocking Graphics Card SLI crafting at the Workbench. The instructions are simple enough to follow, even without electronics knowledge.

There's a mysterious figure on the hillside near the Farm Town dock. He never shows his face, but often sells good stuff—like vodka. Go have a word with him, and bring me back a bottle. Oh, and withdraw some cash from the ATM first—he only deals in cash.
A powerful grenade charged with electricity. Deals electric damage that ignores armor, especially effective against mechanical enemies.
Filled with fuel—ignites the ground on impact.
Head\ to\ the\ spaceship\ and\ install\ the\ Navigation\ System\.

I've\ stashed\ some\ cargo\ at\ the\ Makeshift\ Construction\ Site\ in\ Farm\ Town\.\ It's\ the\ kind\ of\ stuff\ that\ has\ to\ be\ moved\ at\ night\.\ But\ lately\ a\ rogue\ red\ spider's\ been\ messing\ things\ up\.\ Take\ care\ of\ it\ for\ me,\ and\ I'll\ cut\ you\ in\ on\ the\ goods\.

The\ StG-77\ works\ great\ in\ your\ hands,\ but\ other\ customers\ are\ still\ on\ the\ fence\.\ I\ need\ some\ flashier\ results\.\ Use\ it\ to\ take\ down\ the\ Security\ Captain\ at\ City\ Hall—that\ should\ prove\ what\ this\ gun\ can\ do\.\ I've\ got\ a\ lot\ of\ stock,\ and\ I\ can't\ afford\ them\ gathering\ dust\.
I've\ got\ arachnophobia,\ and\ these\ Spider-Bots\ keep\ scaring\ me\ out\ of\ my\ wits\ whenever\ I\ go\ night\ fishing\.\ I\ haven't\ dared\ to\ fish\ lately—you've\ got\ to\ help\ me!
Looks like my friend really has gone missing. A black duck once mocked his muscles as useless—it has to be their gang behind this. Let's show them what we gym ducks are made of, with raw muscle!

I\ don't\ believe\ my\ friend's\ really\ gone\.\ Maybe\ something\ happened\ and\ he\ just\ went\ into\ hiding\.\ Try\ leaving\ some\ protein\ powder\ at\ a\ few\ spots—by\ my\ house\ in\ Ground\ Zero,\ at\ the\ lakeside\ pier\ with\ the\ tank\ truck\ in\ the\ Warehouse\ Area,\ and\ in\ front\ of\ the\ statue\ at\ Farm\ Town's\ City\ Hall's\ plaza\.\ No\ gym\ duck\ can\ resist\ the\ lure\ of\ protein\ powder\.
Place Protein Powder in Ground Zero
Place Protein Powder in Warehouse Area
Place Protein Powder in Farm Town

There's a dangerous guy in Farm Town carrying lots of grenades and incendiary bullets. I need you to take him out. He's usually seen near the Makeshift Construction Site or the Gas Station by the Mercenary Camp.
Reel in the rod when the circles overlap!
You need a fishing rod to fish.
These two lumber mills are crawling with strange types. Even if I took them over, they wouldn't fetch a good price. This won't do—they need to be cleared out.
I\ got\ the\ Blueprint\ for\ the\ AK-103,\ but\ I\ still\ need\ materials\ and\ funds\ to\ build\ it\.\ That\ costs\ money,\ you\ know\.
Now\ that\ it's\ complete,\ test\ its\ power\.\ Head\ to\ Farm\ Town\ and\ take\ down\ some\ Black\ Ducks\.
High-grade ingredients that call for special cooking methods.
Please don't use it for anything... weird.
Low in calories—a favorite among ​fitness enthusiast​s.
Poke a hole and enjoy the sweet coconut water inside.
A great source of energy—perfect as a staple food.
Crisp and refreshing. Famous as a so-called negative calorie food.
Tasty, and can even be made into wine.
Looks like a green onion, but with a milder taste.
Sour, but there's no drink it doesn't go with.
Just the thought of cutting it brings tears to your eyes.
Juicy, and said to soothe the lungs and ease coughs.
Sweet and tangy, but best soaked in salt water before eating.
Cut it open to reveal a beautiful star.
A versatile vegetable—great in all kinds of dishes, and tasty even raw.
Bright blue and flat-bodied, always lively.
Tiny, all-purple, and full of energy.
Its meat is especially tender and delicious.
The red fins are quite eye-catching.
With hard scales and a square mouth, it has a goofy charm.
Long and slender, usually seen in schools.
Round and plump, with tender, tasty meat.
They cluster tightly underwater, looking like one giant fish from above.
Covered in shimmering scales that catch the eye.
Plump and pale, with especially delicious meat.
Has a pointed mouth and a flag-like dorsal fin.
Speckled with spots, considered quite a prized fish.
Covered in spines, it puffs into a spiky ball when startled.
Marked with dark stripes, they often swim in schools.
Blue-green fins contrast sharply with its orange body.
Its body is mottled with green and yellow patches.
Small in size, but swims fiercely.
With a long, thick mouth that looks imposing.
A common ornamental fish that's very popular.
Yellow and green patterned, a striking color mix.
It's so cute that you can't help but take another look.
Brown-and-white patterned, usually found in schools.
It may just be a yellow goldfish, but its name is especially charming.

See\ the\ storm\ countdown\ in\ Base\?\ Every\ ten\ days,\ the\ whole\ planet\ gets\ hit\ by\ a\ 24-hour\ space\ storm\.\ Only\ a\ few\ safe\ zones\ survive\ it\.\ During\ the\ first\ 12\ hours—"Disturbance"—you\ can\ barely\ survive\ inside\.\ Mud\ seems\ to\ have\ some\ kind\ of\ resistance\.\ But\ during\ the\ final\ 12\ hours—"Distortion"—it's\ practically\ certain\ death\.\ Despite\ the\ danger,\ the\ storm's\ energy\ is\ of\ great\ research\ value\.\ I\ need\ samples\.\ During\ the\ "Disturbance"\ phase,\ collect\ some\ samples\ from\ a\ high\ point—the\ hillside\ near\ the\ Fishing\ Dock\ in\ Farm\ Town\ will\ do\.
Collect samples using the Plastic Barrel at the hilltop.

The research has gone smoothly so far, but our experiments will need an ever-growing supply of Space Crystals. We need a more efficient way to deal with the Storm Creatures. Fire-based weapons should be especially effective against them. There's a Shotgunner in Farm Town—the one often lingering near the Radar Station—who happens to carry a fire weapon. Get it for me and I'll see if I can make a copy. And while you're at it, give it a try yourself.
Used at the workbench to develop: TOZ-66 Dragon's Breath.
A Glick that Xiaoming has infused with space energy through a special technique. While its performance remains unchanged, it now fires space bullets.
I've found a technique to infuse weapons with space energy, but I need a few small weapons to test it on. Do you have any spares? A Glick would do.
The space energy infusion was a success, but the yield rate is still too low. I need more raw materials to refine the process.
Now that you've got the right tools, it's time to show your skills. I'm counting on you for the experiment materials.
J-Lab conducted extensive research on space storms before leaving. If you can find some data, it would largely boost my research.

J-Lab\ developed\ a\ new\ class\ of\ firearms\ powered\ by\ Storm\ Matter\.\ In\ terms\ of\ sheer\ firepower,\ they\ are\ not\ much\ stronger\ than\ conventional\ gunpowder\.\ However,\ by\ selling\ these\ energy\ weapons,\ J-Lab\ secured\ massive\ profits,\ which\ funded\ their\ spacecraft\ research\.

We've\ launched\ a\ spacecraft\ development\ program\ based\ on\ our\ Storm\ Area\ discoveries\.\ It\ is\ divided\ into\ several\ parts:\ propulsion,\ thrust,\ navigation,\ life\ support,\ defense,\ and\ computing\ systems\.

This\ solid,\ purple\ matter\ emerges\ alongside\ rifts\.\ The\ air\ in\ the\ Storm\ Area\ contains\ high\ concentrations\ of\ its\ particles\.\ Storm\ Matter\ tends\ to\ accumulate\ inside\ living\ organisms,\ crystallizing\ over\ time\.

J-Lab\ discovered\ that\ purified\ Storm\ Matter\ transforms\ into\ blue\ crystals\.\ These\ crystals\ are\ more\ stable,\ easier\ to\ use,\ and\ free\ from\ the\ harmful\ effects\ on\ living\ beings\.\ Before\ the\ Storm,\ J-Lab\ could\ already\ produce\ such\ crystals,\ but\ only\ through\ cloning\ technology\.\ The\ process\ was\ extremely\ inefficient,\ and\ many\ researchers\ strongly\ opposed\ it\.
A\ helmet\ crafted\ from\ special\ materials\.\ Poor\ at\ stopping\ bullets,\ but\ resistant\ to\ early-stage\ space\ storm\ disturbances\.

Have\ you\ found\ a\ way\ into\ the\ Storm\ Area\?\ It's\ extremely\ dangerous\ with\ constant\ Level\ 2\ Space\ Storms\.\ Make\ thorough\ preparations\ before\ entering\.\ Once\ inside,\ go\ straight\ ahead\ and\ the\ first\ makeshift\ camp\ on\ your\ left\ has\ the\ Storm\ Area\ beacon\.
We've\ secured\ the\ Defense\ Field,\ but\ it's\ complicated\ and\ we\ need\ its\ operation\ manual\.\ Source\ says,\ it\ can\ be\ found\ in\ the\ prison\ on\ the\ south\ side\ of\ J-lab's\ B2\.

You've\ found\ their\ locations\.\ Now\ find\ a\ way\ to\ get\ their\ equipment\.

This\ place\ is\ empty,\ but\ it\ makes\ a\ decent\ hideout\.\ I\ moved\ in\ some\ basic\ gear—at\ least\ it's\ a\ start\.\ Hopefully,\ we\ can\ get\ out\ of\ here\ in\ one\ piece\.\nI\ hired\ someone\ who\ looks\ competent\.\ Time\ to\ put\ him\ to\ the\ test\.

To\ improve\ security,\ all\ guards\ should\ train\ using\ the\ following\ tips:\n1\.\ Hold\ the\ right\ mouse\ button\ to\ aim\ for\ better\ accuracy\.\n2\.\ Aim\ for\ the\ enemy's\ head\ before\ firing\ to\ land\ a\ more\ lethal\ shot\.

As\ long\ as\ we\ all\ rush\ in\ together,\ nobody\ stands\ a\ chance\.\nWhen\ our\ red\ flare\ goes\ up,\ that's\ our\ cue\ to\ strike\.\ If\ they\ don't\ roll\ with\ the\ spacebar,\ one\ slash\ and\ they're\ done\.\ Hahahaha!\nNo\ one's\ better\ than\ us!\ I\ love\ it!

Pack\ up\ and\ head\ home\ once\ you've\ got\ enough\.\ That\ way,\ you\ won't\ screw\ things\ up\.\ If\ you\ don't\ get\ greedy,\ you'll\ always\ come\ out\ with\ something\.\nPicked\ up\ two\ apples\ today\.\ That\ was\ good\.
If\ you\ see\ a\ white\ guy\ out\ here,\ don't\ mess\ with\ him\.\nDon't\ ask\ me\ how\ I\ know\ that\.

Those\ J-Lab\ bastards\ promised\ to\ take\ us\ with\ them,\ but\ they\ broke\ their\ word\.
Now,\ no\ one\ can\ stop\ us\.\ I\ stole\ some\ good\ stuff\ from\ J-Lab\ and\ set\ up\ camp\ in\ Ground\ Zero\.
Here\ in\ Ground\ Zero,\ I,\ Pato\ Chapo,\ call\ the\ shots\.
Still\ don't\ get\ how\ that\ teleport\ beacon\ next\ door\ works\.\ Doesn't\ look\ too\ reliable\ to\ me\.

I've\ been\ watching\ for\ a\ few\ days—the\ Road\ Camp\ folks\ seem\ off\.\nTheir\ leader\ glows\ with\ fire\.\ Doesn't\ look\ like\ someone\ you\ want\ to\ mess\ with\.\nUnless\ you're\ fully\ prepared,\ stay\ away\ from\ them\.

In\ the\ Warehouse\ Area,\ there's\ often\ a\ vicious\ dog\ roaming\ around\.\ Its\ master\ is\ a\ sniper—always\ scheming\ and\ striking\ from\ the\ shadows\.\ If\ you\ spot\ that\ dog,\ you'd\ better\ hide\ immediately\.
Friends\ from\ Ground\ Zero\ also\ told\ me\ about\ another\ guy\ who's\ been\ showing\ up\ there\ with\ a\ dog\.\ Sometimes,\ the\ poor\ puppy\ is\ even\ strapped\ with\ a\ massive\ crate\.
It's\ a\ clear\ sign\ of\ moral\ decay—this\ guy\ is\ even\ worse\ than\ Lordon\.
I\ have\ a\ bad\ feeling\ about\ this\.
They\ said\ they\ would\ come\ back\ for\ me\.

I\ dug\ a\ secret\ tunnel\ to\ the\ warehouse,\ a\ way\ to\ bypass\ the\ Speedy\ Group\ Commander's\ guards\.\ I\ know\ there\ are\ valuables\ inside,\ and\ I'm\ gonna\ get\ them\.\nI\ ran\ into\ a\ blue-skinned\ guy\ in\ the\ tunnel—he\ seemed\ to\ be\ hiding\ many\ secrets\.

We\ were\ stationed\ here\ to\ guard\ the\ warehouse,\ but\ those\ J-Lab\ guys\ think\ I\ don't\ know\ what's\ stored\ inside\.
Those\ sleep\ pods\ are\ amazing\.\ I\ tried\ one\ for\ a\ while\.\ My\ skin\ felt\ smooth,\ almost\ glowing\.
I\ placed\ one\ in\ the\ Warehouse\ office\ and\ another\ in\ my\ house\ in\ the\ eastern\ town\.

The\ blue\ guy\ told\ me\ how\ to\ make\ Cola\ taste\ even\ better\.\nThe\ raw\ material\ is\ a\ strange\ blue\ cube\.\ Once\ processed,\ it\ becomes\ a\ green\ volatile\ liquid\ he\ called\ "Cola\ Concentrate\."\ It's\ corrosive\ and\ undrinkable\ in\ its\ raw\ form,\ but\ after\ simple\ treatment\ it\ transforms\ into\ the\ most\ delicious\ cola\ imaginable\.\ Not\ too\ sweet,\ but\ irresistibly\ addictive\.\ If\ we\ could\ sell\ it,\ it\ would\ surely\ fly\ off\ the\ shelves\.\nThe\ problem\ is\.\.\.\ how\ to\ obtain\ this\ blue\ cube\.\.\.

Sleep\ devices\ produced\ using\ products\ of\ the\ rifts,\ consisting\ of\ two\ components\.\ One\ is\ a\ Storm\ Matter-made\ drug\ that\ greatly\ enhances\ biological\ adaptability\.\ The\ other\ is\ a\ pod\ built\ with\ storm\ tech\ to\ improve\ sleep\ quality\.\nEarly\ models\ suffered\ from\ impurities\ in\ the\ purification\ process\ of\ Storm\ Matter\.\ So\ users\ would\ experience\ side\ effects,\ primarily\ impulsiveness,\ irritability,\ and\ violent\ tendencies\.

To\ ensure\ that\ various\ experiments\ in\ the\ Storm\ Area\ proceeded\ without\ interference,\ J-Lab\ required\ combat\ strength\ to\ secure\ the\ test\ sites\.\ They\ recruited\ a\ group\ of\ volunteers\ for\ body\ modification\.\ In\ the\ first\ round,\ J-Lab\ created\ "Koko\ Koko,"\ a\ terrifying\ war\ machine\ infused\ with\ storm\ power\.\ However,\ it\ proved\ extremely\ unstable\ and\ difficult\ to\ control\.\ J-Lab\ then\ optimized\ the\ process\ and,\ in\ the\ second\ round,\ developed\ four\ new\ test\ subjects\ under\ the\ codename\ Four\ Horsemen,\ intended\ to\ restrain\ "Koko\ Koko\."\nEven\ these\ new\ prototypes\ remain\ unstable\.

Some\ employees\ are\ showing\ poor\ work\ attitudes\.\nOne\ employee,\ Jeff,\ is\ often\ caught\ sneaking\ off\ to\ the\ screening\ room\ during\ work\ hours\ to\ play\ games\.\ We\ plan\ to\ dismiss\ him\.\nXiaoming\ as\ well\.

In\ the\ Storm\ Area,\ we\ discovered\ a\ small\ craft\ containing\ the\ corpse\ of\ what\ appeared\ to\ be\ an\ alien\ lifeform\.

After\ decryption,\ the\ following\ was\ revealed:
"During\ our\ travels,\ we\ discovered\ this\ planet\.\ Its\ core\ was\ rich\ in\ life\ energy,\ an\ excellent\ source\ of\ raw\ material,\ so\ we\ began\ extraction\.

To\ accelerate\ spacecraft\ production,\ we\ ramped\ up\ crystal\ extraction\.\nBut\ as\ extraction\ increases,\ the\ rift\ collapse\ accelerates\ too\.\ I\ fear\ the\ whole\ planet\ may\ break\ apart\ before\ we\ can\ produce\ enough\ ships\.
